\date{2025-02-22}
\title{Coherent Equivalences}
\taxon{Module}

\import{stt-macros}

% ```agda
\agda{
module Foundations.CoherentEquivalences where

open import Foundations.Universes
open import Foundations.QuasiEquivalences
open import Foundations.Sigma
open import Foundations.Functions
open import Foundations.FunctionInverses
open import Foundations.Homotopy
open import Foundations.Identity
open import Foundations.IdentityReasoning
}
% ```

\p{
We can upgrade a [quasi-equivalence](Foundations.QuasiEquivalences) into a
homotopy-correct equivalence by adding an extra coherence condition, that makes being
an equivalence into a proposition.
}

\subtree[stt-000K]{
\taxon{Remark}
\title{Half-adjoint equivalence}

\p{The definition of a quasi-equivalence involves:}

\ul{
\li{#{f : A \to B}}
\li{#{g : B \to A}}
\li{#{\eta : f \circ g = \id}}
\li{#{\varepsilon : \id = g \circ f}}
}

\p{The names #{\eta} and #{\varepsilon} remind us that this looks like the data of an adjunction. But we are missing the laws, often called the zig-zag laws. One of which state that the following 2-cell contracts to the identity:
}

\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#
\begin{tikzcd}
	A &&&& A \\
	\\
	&& B &&&& B
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, no head, from=1-1, to=1-5]
	\arrow["\id", shift left, no head, from=1-1, to=1-5]
	\arrow["f"', from=1-1, to=3-3]
	\arrow["f"', from=1-5, to=3-7]
	\arrow["g"', from=3-3, to=1-5]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\id"', no head, from=3-3, to=3-7]
	\arrow[shift left, no head, from=3-3, to=3-7]
	\arrow["\varepsilon", shorten <=7pt, shorten >=11pt, Rightarrow, from=0, to=3-3]
	\arrow["\eta", shorten <=7pt, shorten >=7pt, Rightarrow, from=1-5, to=1]
\end{tikzcd}
}

\p{In symbols, this is: #{f \cdot \varepsilon \circ \eta \cdot f = \id} (where #{\cdot} denotes horizontal composition and #{\circ} denotes vertical composition).}
}

\p{Note that in our formalisation #{\varepsilon} is a 2-cell in the opposite direction, but since all 2-cells are invertible, this makes no difference to the definition and makes the formalisation slightly smoother.}

\subtree[stt-001R]{
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Coherence data for [quasi-equivalences](Foundations.QuasiEquivalences)}

% ```agda
\agda{
qinv-coh : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B} вҶ’ quasi-inv f вҶ’ Type (рқ“Ө вҠ” рқ“Ҙ)
qinv-coh {f = f} (g , Оө , О·) = f в—Ӯ Оө ~ О· в–ё f
}
% ```
}

\subtree[stt-001U]{
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Equivalences}


\p{Of the many equivalent notions of equivalences in HoTT, we will single out coherent equivalences as the default one in the library.}

% ```agda
\agda{
record is-equiv {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} (f : A вҶ’ B) : Type (рқ“Ө вҠ” рқ“Ҙ) where
  constructor mk-eqv
  field
    qinv     : quasi-inv f
    coherent : qinv-coh qinv

  qeqv : A вүҠ B
  qeqv = mkвүҠ f qinv

  open _вүҠ_ qeqv public hiding (fwd)

  Оө : f вҲҳ bwd ~ id
  Оө x = section-fwd .snd x

  ОөвҒ»В№ : id ~ f вҲҳ bwd
  ОөвҒ»В№ = Оө ~вҒ»В№

  О· : bwd вҲҳ f ~ id
  О· x = retraction-fwd .snd x

  О·вҒ»В№ : id ~ bwd вҲҳ f
  О·вҒ»В№ = О· ~вҒ»В№

  cohвҒ»В№ :  (f в—Ӯ О·вҒ»В№) ~ (ОөвҒ»В№ в–ё f)
  cohвҒ»В№ a = ap-sym f (О· a) вҲҷ ap sym (coherent a)

  swizzle-bwd
    : вҲҖ {рқ“Ұ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
        (g : C вҶ’ B) (h : C вҶ’ A)
      вҶ’ g ~ f вҲҳ h вҶ’ bwd вҲҳ g ~ h
  swizzle-bwd g h K = bwd в—Ӯ K ~вҲҷ О· в–ё h
}
% ```

\p{We also define the packaged version of an equivalence together with the proof of it being an equivalence}

% ```agda
\agda{
infix 7 _вүғ_
record _вүғ_ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} (A : Type рқ“Ө) (B : Type рқ“Ҙ) : Type (рқ“Ө вҠ” рқ“Ҙ) where
  constructor mkвүғ
  field
    fwd : A вҶ’ B
    has-is-eqv : is-equiv fwd

  open is-equiv has-is-eqv public

qinvвҶҗis-equiv
  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B} вҶ’ is-equiv f вҶ’ quasi-inv f
qinvвҶҗis-equiv = is-equiv.qinv

qeqvвҶҗequiv
  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ A вүҠ B
qeqvвҶҗequiv (mkвүғ _ has-is-eqv) = qeqv where open is-equiv has-is-eqv
}
% ```
}



\subtree[stt-000J]{
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{Quasi-equivalences can be made coherent}
% HoTT book. 4.2.3

\p{Every quasi-equivalence can be upgraded to a coherent equivalence.}

\proof{
\p{Since we (are soon to) know that being an equivalence is a proposition, and that quasi-equivalences aren't equivalent to equivalences,
we know that whatever the map is, it cannot be a section of the obvious map #{\textrm{is-equiv}(f) \to \textrm{quasi-inv}(f)}, and so as a
result we know we will have to be a bit clever about how we choose the 2-cells of our coherent equivalence.}

\p{The proof goes through by cooking up a 2-cell #{\varepsilon} that makes the coherence go through trivially.
Working backwards, we need an #{\varepsilon '} such that #{\varepsilon' f = \eta f}. }


\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#
\begin{tikzcd}
	fgf &&&&&& f \\
	&&&& fgf \\
	& fgfgf \\
	&&&&& fgf
	\arrow["{f\eta}", from=1-1, to=1-7]
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, equals, from=1-1, to=2-5]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon^{-1} fgf}"', from=1-1, to=3-2]
	\arrow["{f\eta}"', from=2-5, to=1-7]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon fgf}", from=3-2, to=2-5]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{fgf \eta}", from=3-2, to=4-6]
	\arrow[""{name=2, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{f\eta gf}"', bend right,from=3-2, to=4-6]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon f}"', bend right, from=4-6, to=1-7]
	\arrow["2", shorten <=11pt, shorten >=8pt, Rightarrow, from=4-6, to=2-5]
	\arrow["1"', shorten <=11pt, shorten >=11pt, Rightarrow, from=3-2, to=0]
	\arrow["3"', shorten <=2pt, shorten >=2pt, Rightarrow, from=2, to=1]
\end{tikzcd}
}


\p{
Consider the above diagram, and in particular note that the lower boundary is given by morphisms of the form #{\alpha f} for some alpha.
By taking the horizontal composition of these #{\alpha}'s gives us our desired #{\epsilon' := \varepsilon^{-1} fg \cdot f \eta g \cdot \varepsilon}. It satisfies the necessary equations by the vertical composite of the cells:
}

\ol{
\li{Trivially follows from paths forming groupoids.}
\li{The naturality of homotopies.}
\li{\citet{2.4.3}{HoTT} [[stt-001O]]}
}

% ```agda
\agda{
is-equivвҶҗqinv : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B} вҶ’ quasi-inv f вҶ’ is-equiv f
is-equivвҶҗqinv {f = f} (g , О· , Оө) = mk-eqv (g , О· , Оө') coh where opaque
  Оө' : f вҲҳ g ~ id
  Оө' = (Оө ~вҒ»В№) в–ё f в–ё g ~вҲҷ
       f в—Ӯ О· в–ё g       ~вҲҷ
       Оө

  lem3 : g в—Ӯ f в—Ӯ О· ~ О· в–ё g в–ё f
  lem3 x = sym (ap-вҲҳ g f (О· x)) вҲҷ n where
    n : (g вҲҳ f в—Ӯ О·) x пјқ (О· в–ё g в–ё f) x
    n = sym (homotopy-inverse (g вҲҳ f) О· x)

  lem2 : Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҲҷ f в—Ӯ О· ~ f в—Ӯ g в—Ӯ f в—Ӯ О· ~вҲҷ Оө в–ё f
  lem2 x = I вҲҷ ap (_вҲҷ (Оө (f x))) (ap-вҲҳ f g (ap f (О· x))) where
    I : Оө (f (g (f x))) вҲҷ (ap f (О· x)) пјқ
         ap (О» z вҶ’ (f вҲҳ g) z) (ap f (О· x)) вҲҷ Оө (f x)
    I = ap (Оө (f (g (f x))) вҲҷ_) (sym (ap-id (ap f (О· x)))) вҲҷ
        homotopy-natural Оө {f (g (f x))} (ap f (О· x))

  lem1 : f в—Ӯ О· ~
           ((Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) ~вҲҷ Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҲҷ f в—Ӯ О·)
  lem1 a = вҲҷ.insertr _ {h = Оө (f (g (f a)))} {i = sym (Оө (f (g (f a))))} (вҲҷ-sym' (Оө (f (g (f a))))) {_} {ap f (О· a)}


  coh : qinv-coh (g , О· , Оө')
  coh = (f в—Ӯ О·)
          ~вҹЁ lem1 вҹ©
        (Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) ~вҲҷ Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҲҷ f в—Ӯ О·
          ~вҹЁ ~refl: (Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) вҹ©~вҲҷвҹЁ lem2 вҹ©
        (Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) ~вҲҷ f в—Ӯ g в—Ӯ f в—Ӯ О· ~вҲҷ Оө в–ё f
          ~вҹЁ ~refl: (Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) вҹ©~вҲҷвҹЁ f вҹ©~в—ӮвҹЁ lem3 вҹ©~вҲҷвҹЁ ~refl: Оө в–ё f вҹ©
        (Оө в–ё f в–ё g в–ё f ~вҒ»В№) ~вҲҷ f в—Ӯ О· в–ё g в–ё f ~вҲҷ Оө в–ё f
          ~вҹЁвҹ©
         Оө' в–ё f
          ~вҲҺ

equivвҶҗqequiv : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ A вүҠ B вҶ’ A вүғ B
equivвҶҗqequiv (mkвүҠ fwd fwd-qinv) = mkвүғ fwd (is-equivвҶҗqinv fwd-qinv)

вүғ-repвүҠ  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ (A вүғ B) вүҠ ОЈ (A вҶ’ B) is-equiv
вүғ-repвүҠ ._вүҠ_.fwd (mkвүғ f e) = f , e
вүғ-repвүҠ ._вүҠ_.fwd-qinv .fst (f , e) = mkвүғ f e
вүғ-repвүҠ ._вүҠ_.fwd-qinv .snd .fst _ = refl
вүғ-repвүҠ ._вүҠ_.fwd-qinv .snd .snd _ = refl

вүғ-rep : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ (A вүғ B) вүғ ОЈ (A вҶ’ B) is-equiv
вүғ-rep = equivвҶҗqequiv вүғ-repвүҠ
}
% ```
}
}

\subtree[stt-005T]{
\date{2025-06-19}
\title{Assuming the codomain to construct an equivalence}
\taxon{Theorem}
  \p{To show that a function is an equivalence,
  it suffices show that it is an equivalence assuming a point
  in the codomain.}

%```agda
\agda{
is-equivвҶҗis-equiv-if-cod
  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө}
      {B : Type рқ“Ҙ}
      {f : A вҶ’ B}
     вҶ’ (B вҶ’ is-equiv f)
     вҶ’ is-equiv f
is-equivвҶҗis-equiv-if-cod {f = f} feqb
  = is-equivвҶҗqinv
      ( (О» b вҶ’ bwd (feqb b) b)
      , (О» a вҶ’ О· (feqb (f a)) a)
      , О» b вҶ’ Оө (feqb b) b )
    where open is-equiv
}
%```
}


\subtree[stt-001T]{
\title{Equivalences form an #{\infty}-groupoid over types}
\author{samueltoth}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-04-23}

\p{
We show that equivalence forms a reflexive, transitive and symmetric relation on
types. More concretely, we show the identity map is an equivalence, that equivalences
compose, and that equivalences may be inverted. We construct each explicitly to
maintain control over the section and retraction homotopies.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
id-is-equiv : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A : Type рқ“Ө} вҶ’ is-equiv (id: A)
id-is-equiv = mk-eqv (id , ~refl , ~refl) ~refl

idвүғ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A : Type рқ“Ө} вҶ’ A вүғ A
idвүғ = mkвүғ id id-is-equiv

idвүғ: : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} (A : Type рқ“Ө) вҶ’ A вүғ A
idвүғ: A = idвүғ
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv
  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
      {f : B вҶ’ C} {g : A вҶ’ B}
  вҶ’ is-equiv f вҶ’ is-equiv g
  вҶ’ quasi-inv (f вҲҳ g)
is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv {f = f} {g} fe ge .fst
  = is-equiv.bwd ge вҲҳ is-equiv.bwd fe
is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv {f = f} {g} fe ge .snd .fst
  = is-equiv.bwd ge в—Ӯ is-equiv.О· fe в–ё g ~вҲҷ is-equiv.О· ge
is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv {f = f} {g} fe ge .snd .snd
  = f в—Ӯ is-equiv.Оө ge в–ё is-equiv.bwd fe ~вҲҷ is-equiv.Оө fe

opaque
  is-equiv-вҲҳ-coh
    : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
        {f : B вҶ’ C} {g : A вҶ’ B}
      (fe : is-equiv f) (ge : is-equiv g)
    вҶ’ qinv-coh (is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv fe ge)
  is-equiv-вҲҳ-coh {f = f} {g} fe ge = coh where
    module ef = is-equiv fe
    module eg = is-equiv ge

    ret : eg.bwd вҲҳ ef.bwd вҲҳ f вҲҳ g ~ id
    ret = is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv fe ge .snd .fst

    sec : f вҲҳ g вҲҳ eg.bwd вҲҳ ef.bwd ~ id
    sec = is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv fe ge .snd .snd

    cohвӮҒ
      : вҲҖ a
      вҶ’ ap (f вҲҳ g) (ret a)
      пјқ ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a)) вҲҷ eg.Оө (g a))
    cohвӮҒ a
      = ap (f вҲҳ g) (ret a)
          пјқвҹЁ ap-вҲҷ (f вҲҳ g) (ap eg.bwd (ef.О· (g a))) (eg.О· a) вҹ©
        ap (f вҲҳ g) (ap eg.bwd (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ ap (f вҲҳ g) (eg.О· a)
          пјқвҹЁ ap (_вҲҷ ap (f вҲҳ g) (eg.О· a)) (ap-вҲҳ f g (ap eg.bwd (ef.О· (g a)))) вҹ©
        ap f (ap g (ap eg.bwd (ef.О· (g a)))) вҲҷ ap (f вҲҳ g) (eg.О· a)
          пјқвҹЁ ap (_вҲҷ ap (f вҲҳ g) (eg.О· a)) (ap (ap f) (sym (ap-вҲҳ g eg.bwd (ef.О· (g a))))) вҹ©
        ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ ap (f вҲҳ g) (eg.О· a)
          пјқвҹЁ ap (ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ_) (ap-вҲҳ f g (eg.О· a)) вҹ©
        ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ ap f (ap g (eg.О· a))
          пјқвҹЁ ap (ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ_) (ap (ap f) (eg.coherent a)) вҹ©
        ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) вҲҷ ap f (eg.Оө (g a))
          пјқвҹЁ sym (ap-вҲҷ f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a))) (eg.Оө (g a))) вҹ©
        ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a)) вҲҷ eg.Оө (g a))
          вҲҺ

    cohвӮӮ
      : вҲҖ a
      вҶ’ ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a)) вҲҷ eg.Оө (g a))
      пјқ ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ ap f (ef.О· (g a))
    cohвӮӮ a
      = ap f (ap (g вҲҳ eg.bwd) (ef.О· (g a)) вҲҷ eg.Оө (g a))
          пјқвҹЁ ap (ap f)
               ( sym (homotopy-natural eg.Оө (ef.О· (g a)))
               вҲҷ ap (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a))) вҲҷ_) (ap-id (ef.О· (g a)))) вҹ©
        ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a))) вҲҷ ef.О· (g a))
          пјқвҹЁ ap-вҲҷ f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) (ef.О· (g a)) вҹ©
        ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ ap f (ef.О· (g a))
          вҲҺ

    cohвӮғ
      : вҲҖ a
      вҶ’ ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ ap f (ef.О· (g a))
      пјқ sec (f (g a))
    cohвӮғ a
      = ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ ap f (ef.О· (g a))
          пјқвҹЁ ap (ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ_) (ef.coherent (g a)) вҹ©
        ap f (eg.Оө (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вҲҷ ef.Оө (f (g a))
          пјқвҹЁвҹ©
        sec (f (g a))
          вҲҺ

    coh : qinv-coh (is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv fe ge)
    coh a = cohвӮҒ a вҲҷ cohвӮӮ a вҲҷ cohвӮғ a

is-equiv-вҲҳ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
                  {f : B вҶ’ C} {g : A вҶ’ B} вҶ’
                  is-equiv f вҶ’ is-equiv g
                  вҶ’ is-equiv (f вҲҳ g)
is-equiv-вҲҳ fe ge = mk-eqv (is-equiv-вҲҳ-qinv fe ge) (is-equiv-вҲҳ-coh fe ge)

equiv-comp : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
             вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ B вүғ C вҶ’ A вүғ C
equiv-comp (mkвүғ f e) (mkвүғ g e') = mkвүғ (g вҲҳ f) (is-equiv-вҲҳ e' e)
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
is-equivвҒ»В№-qinv
  : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B}
  вҶ’ (e : is-equiv f)
  вҶ’ quasi-inv (is-equiv.bwd e)
is-equivвҒ»В№-qinv e = bwd-qinv (qinvвҶҗis-equiv e)

opaque
  is-equivвҒ»В№-coh
    : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B}
    вҶ’ (e : is-equiv f)
    вҶ’ qinv-coh (is-equivвҒ»В№-qinv e)
  is-equivвҒ»В№-coh {A = A} {f = f} e = coh where
    open is-equiv e using (bwd; О·; Оө; coherent)

    qinv : quasi-inv bwd
    qinv = is-equivвҒ»В№-qinv e

    unap-ap-f
      : вҲҖ {x y : A} {p q : x пјқ y}
      вҶ’ ap f p пјқ ap f q
      вҶ’ p пјқ q

    unap-ap-f {x} {y}
      = is-injectiveвҶҗretraction-witness
          (is-injectiveвҶҗretraction-witness bwd О· {x} {y})
          (ap-retraction-witness bwd О· {x} {y})

    cohвӮҒ : вҲҖ b
      вҶ’ ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) пјқ Оө (f (bwd b))
    cohвӮҒ b
      = ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b)
          пјқвҹЁ sym (вҲҷ-reflr (ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b))) вҹ©
        ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ refl
          пјқвҹЁ ap (ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ_) (sym (вҲҷ-sym (Оө b))) вҹ©
        ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ (Оө b вҲҷ sym (Оө b))
          пјқвҹЁ sym (вҲҷ-assoc (ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b)) (Оө b) (sym (Оө b))) вҹ©
        (ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ Оө b) вҲҷ sym (Оө b)
          пјқвҹЁ ap ((ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ Оө b) вҲҷ_) (sym (ap sym (ap-id (Оө b)))) вҹ©
        (ap (f вҲҳ bwd) (Оө b) вҲҷ Оө b) вҲҷ sym (ap id (Оө b))
          пјқвҹЁ homotopy-cancel Оө (Оө b) вҹ©
        Оө (f (bwd b))
          вҲҺ

    cohвӮӮ : вҲҖ b
      вҶ’ ap f (ap bwd (Оө b)) пјқ Оө (f (bwd b))
    cohвӮӮ b = sym (ap-вҲҳ f bwd (Оө b)) вҲҷ cohвӮҒ b

    cohвӮғ : вҲҖ b
      вҶ’ Оө (f (bwd b)) пјқ ap f (О· (bwd b))
    cohвӮғ b = sym (coherent (bwd b))

    coh : qinv-coh qinv
    coh b = unap-ap-f (cohвӮӮ b вҲҷ cohвӮғ b)

is-equivвҒ»В№ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {f : A вҶ’ B}
             вҶ’ (e : is-equiv f) вҶ’ is-equiv (is-equiv.bwd e)
is-equivвҒ»В№ e = mk-eqv (is-equivвҒ»В№-qinv e) (is-equivвҒ»В№-coh e)
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
equivвҶҗId : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A B : Type рқ“Ө} вҶ’ A пјқ B вҶ’ A вүғ B
equivвҶҗId refl = idвүғ

fwd-equivвҶҗId : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A B : Type рқ“Ө} (p : A пјқ B)
               вҶ’ _вүғ_.fwd (equivвҶҗId p) пјқ coe p
fwd-equivвҶҗId refl = refl

coe-is-equiv : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A B : Type рқ“Ө} (p : A пјқ B)
               вҶ’ is-equiv (coe p)
coe-is-equiv refl = id-is-equiv

coeвүғ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө} {A B : Type рқ“Ө} (p : A пјқ B) вҶ’ A вүғ B
coeвүғ p = mkвүғ (coe p) (coe-is-equiv p)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[stt-001S]{
\taxon{Notation}

\title{Reasoning combinators for equivalences}

% ```agda
\agda{
_вҲҷвүғ_ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
             вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ B вүғ C вҶ’ A вүғ C
_вҲҷвүғ_ = equiv-comp

infixl 29 _вҲҷвүғ_

_eвҒ»В№ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} {A : Type рқ“Ө} {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ B вүғ A
(mkвүғ f e)  eвҒ»В№ = mkвүғ (is-equiv.bwd e) (is-equivвҒ»В№ e)

вүғвҹЁвҹ©-syntax : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ рқ“Ұ} (A : Type рқ“Ө) {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} {C : Type рқ“Ұ}
           вҶ’ B вүғ C вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ A вүғ C
вүғвҹЁвҹ©-syntax A g f = equiv-comp f g


_вүғвҹЁвҹ©_ : вҲҖ {рқ“Ө рқ“Ҙ} (A : Type рқ“Ө) {B : Type рқ“Ҙ} вҶ’ A вүғ B вҶ’ A вүғ B
x вүғвҹЁвҹ© xвүғy = xвүғy

_вүғвҲҺ : вҲҖ {в„“} (A : Type в„“) вҶ’ A вүғ A
x вүғвҲҺ = idвүғ

infix 31 _eвҒ»В№

infixr 2 вүғвҹЁвҹ©-syntax _вүғвҹЁвҹ©_
infix  3 _вүғвҲҺ

syntax вүғвҹЁвҹ©-syntax x q p = x вүғвҹЁ p вҹ© q
}
% ```
}
